
[1]sexton

   SEX'TON, n. [contracted from sacristan, which see.] An under officer of
   the church, whose buiness is to take care of the vessels, vestments,
   &c. belonging to the church, to attend on the officiating clergyman and
   perform other duties pertaining to the church, to dig graves, &c.
